Print the first N rows where the i-th row contains the first i capital letters.

Input Format:
The first line contains the number T of test cases.
For each test case:
There is only one line containing N, which is the number of rows in the pattern.

Output Format:
For each test case, print the pattern.

Constraints:
1 ≤ T ≤ 26
1 ≤ N ≤ 26

Sample Input 1:
1
1

Sample Output 1:
A

Sample Input 2:
2
4
7

Sample Output 2:
A
AB
ABC
ABCD
A
AB
ABC
ABCD
ABCDE
ABCDEF
ABCDEFG

Sample Input 3:
1
5

Sample Output 3:
A
AB
ABC
ABCD
ABCDE

Note:
In Sample Input 1, N = 1, so we print one row containing the first 1 capital letter: "A".

In Sample Input 2, N = 5, so we print five rows, each row i contains the first i capital letters.

In Sample Input 3, there are two test cases:
First test case with N = 4, we print the pattern up to "ABCD".
Second test case with N = 7, we print the pattern up to "ABCDEFG".



#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
typedef long long ll;
#define endl "\n"   // optional, better to avoid redefining endl

void solve() {
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    

    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        char ch = 'A';
        for(int j = 0; j <= i; j++)
        {
            cout<<ch;
            ch++;
        }
        cout<<endl;
    }
}

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while (t--) {
        solve();
    }

    return 0;
}
